1
00:00:02,510 --> 00:00:03,510
Hey!

2
00:00:03,750 --> 00:00:04,750
Hurry it up!

3
00:00:05,430 --> 00:00:06,580
I'm working on it!

4
00:00:10,980 --> 00:00:11,980
What are you guys doing?

5
00:00:15,220 --> 00:00:17,960
Hey, what are you looking at?

6
00:00:18,880 --> 00:00:20,080
What the hell is your problem?

7
00:00:28,360 --> 00:00:29,900
This is Fuu's car, isn't it?

8
00:00:31,350 --> 00:00:32,360
You bastard...

9
00:00:41,710 --> 00:00:42,710
Get lost!

10
00:00:58,380 --> 00:00:59,380
What do you want?

11
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:07,100
Get out of here!

12
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:10,200
Damn it.

13
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:41,850
As long as Fuu is safe,

14
00:01:43,550 --> 00:01:44,730
that's all that matters.

15
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:22,679
- That was amazing.
- Yeah.

16
00:02:22,680 --> 00:02:25,430
Man, is it ever going to stop raining?

17
00:02:26,870 --> 00:02:27,990
The car is right over there.

18
00:02:28,030 --> 00:02:30,230
- Thanks.
- Sure, get home safe.

19
00:02:44,930 --> 00:02:46,170
What's with this scratch?

20
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:07,300
"The Boy Next World My Destiny"
(Episode 4)

21
00:03:59,460 --> 00:04:01,050
Did you actually understand that movie?

22
00:04:01,850 --> 00:04:02,850
Not at all.

23
00:04:03,480 --> 00:04:04,480
Oh, but...

24
00:04:04,760 --> 00:04:06,879
that new basil cheese popcorn

25
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:08,060
was incredible, right?

26
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:09,230
It tasted just like pizza.

27
00:04:10,770 --> 00:04:12,890
If you never get them,
why do you always come with me?

28
00:04:14,250 --> 00:04:15,860
Because you're the one asking.

29
00:04:29,880 --> 00:04:31,080
So, how are things with Sara?

30
00:04:33,270 --> 00:04:34,270
Sara?

31
00:04:35,086 --> 00:04:36,086
What about him?

32
00:04:36,310 --> 00:04:37,310
Where's this coming from?

33
00:04:40,650 --> 00:04:41,650
Never mind.

34
00:04:41,730 --> 00:04:42,730
I get it now.

35
00:04:43,410 --> 00:04:44,410
Get what?

36
00:04:47,910 --> 00:04:48,590
Why do you and everyone else

37
00:04:48,591 --> 00:04:50,240
keep asking me about him?

38
00:04:50,290 --> 00:04:51,490
Because we're rooting for you.

39
00:04:52,970 --> 00:04:53,970
That guy

40
00:04:54,750 --> 00:04:55,950
only has eyes for you.

41
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:00,730
We're just happy for you.

42
00:05:01,130 --> 00:05:02,500
You're a great guy,

43
00:05:03,170 --> 00:05:04,329
but you're way too gullible.

44
00:05:04,330 --> 00:05:05,730
You'll believe just about anything.

45
00:05:06,210 --> 00:05:07,410
- Me?
- Yeah.

46
00:05:07,450 --> 00:05:08,300
No way.

47
00:05:08,350 --> 00:05:10,120
Isn't that exactly why he likes you?

48
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:14,220
Sara's friends are pretty simple, too.

49
00:05:15,390 --> 00:05:17,330
Huh? You mean Taiga?

50
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:31,050
Oh, it's raining.

51
00:05:33,690 --> 00:05:34,690
What's wrong?

52
00:05:35,710 --> 00:05:37,600
It started pouring, and I was worried.

53
00:05:38,350 --> 00:05:39,350
You're going to get wet.

54
00:05:40,020 --> 00:05:41,020
It's fine.

55
00:05:57,720 --> 00:05:59,020
Wait, Sara...

56
00:05:59,270 --> 00:06:00,680
Stop... wait a second.

57
00:06:01,190 --> 00:06:02,860
Put me down! Hey, let go!

58
00:06:09,850 --> 00:06:10,850
You're freezing.

59
00:06:13,020 --> 00:06:14,140
What are you doing?

60
00:06:18,710 --> 00:06:20,580
Be good and go take a shower.

61
00:06:28,740 --> 00:06:30,620
How am I supposed to
shower with my clothes on?

62
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:40,480
It's not *this* Fuu's body
you want to see, is it?

63
00:06:48,630 --> 00:06:49,630
Yeah, sorry.

64
00:06:51,830 --> 00:06:55,360
I was just worried about you.

65
00:06:59,700 --> 00:07:00,800
I know.

66
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:05,500
You can go now.

67
00:07:10,380 --> 00:07:11,580
Sara.

68
00:07:15,870 --> 00:07:16,870
Fuu.

69
00:07:33,260 --> 00:07:34,460
Can I kiss you?

70
00:07:44,340 --> 00:07:45,340
Is it okay?

71
00:08:52,980 --> 00:08:54,080
You should leave.

72
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:02,320
I'm happy.

73
00:09:05,210 --> 00:09:06,360
About what?

74
00:09:18,530 --> 00:09:20,360
Looks like we're on the same page.

75
00:09:25,910 --> 00:09:26,910
We are not.

76
00:09:28,130 --> 00:09:29,410
What are you even talking about?

77
00:09:29,580 --> 00:09:30,580
You're always like this,

78
00:09:30,700 --> 00:09:31,980
teasing me every chance you get.

79
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:33,960
First time?

80
00:09:35,090 --> 00:09:36,310
Get out!

81
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:38,720
Just go already!

82
00:09:45,470 --> 00:09:46,470
That's pretty scary.

83
00:09:53,720 --> 00:09:56,290
What do you actually know?

84
00:09:58,280 --> 00:09:59,950
I know you've got secrets.

85
00:10:01,300 --> 00:10:02,500
Then again, so do I.

86
00:10:03,790 --> 00:10:04,790
Sara.

87
00:10:04,870 --> 00:10:06,390
Why did you choose the same uni as Fuu?

88
00:10:12,730 --> 00:10:13,730
I'm surprised.

89
00:10:14,090 --> 00:10:16,250
I didn't think you were
the type to eavesdrop.

90
00:10:20,820 --> 00:10:22,020
How did you know?

91
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:26,320
I asked, and you answered me.

92
00:10:26,710 --> 00:10:27,570
Right here.

93
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:28,570
Are you joking?

94
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:30,330
I'm not joking. It's the truth.

95
00:10:31,860 --> 00:10:32,860
Two years ago,

96
00:10:33,410 --> 00:10:36,440
ever since the day I met Fuu,
I've been able to hear your inner voice.

97
00:10:48,090 --> 00:10:49,380
I won't tell a soul.

98
00:10:49,770 --> 00:10:50,970
Especially not Fuu.

99
00:10:51,530 --> 00:10:53,290
You should be the one to tell him.

100
00:11:07,030 --> 00:11:09,150
Is someone talking behind your back?

101
00:11:09,820 --> 00:11:10,820
No way.

102
00:11:11,063 --> 00:11:12,983
I think I've just had a
cold since this morning.

103
00:11:13,670 --> 00:11:14,670
Oh, really?

104
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:16,520
- Yeah.
- You okay?

105
00:11:16,930 --> 00:11:17,930
Yeah.

106
00:11:18,870 --> 00:11:20,970
You finally made your move, Fuu!

107
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:22,680
Huh?

108
00:11:23,140 --> 00:11:26,030
Making out right in
front of the school gates.

109
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:29,840
Word is you and the Ice Prince
are getting pretty hot and heavy.

110
00:11:31,950 --> 00:11:34,450
Every student here is jealous of you.

111
00:11:35,830 --> 00:11:39,119
Don't tell me you guys have
already gone all the way.

112
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:40,630
Ouch! What was that for?

113
00:11:40,710 --> 00:11:42,340
Stop asking Fuu such gross questions.

114
00:11:43,470 --> 00:11:45,860
Wait, a kiss? For real?

115
00:11:46,190 --> 00:11:47,860
No, we weren't kissing in the street...

116
00:11:50,890 --> 00:11:53,380
So you're saying
you've done it somewhere else?

117
00:11:53,580 --> 00:11:54,580
Hmm?

118
00:11:58,100 --> 00:11:59,300
Could you back off a bit?

119
00:12:00,320 --> 00:12:02,019
We're heading out.

120
00:12:02,020 --> 00:12:03,030
Oh, wait up!

121
00:12:03,110 --> 00:12:05,750
Tell me everything! Now
I'm even more curious.

122
00:12:07,590 --> 00:12:09,390
- So what's the deal with you two?
- Let's go.

123
00:12:10,350 --> 00:12:12,060
- What's the deal?
- Bye!

124
00:12:12,390 --> 00:12:13,390
Come on, tell me!

125
00:12:18,100 --> 00:12:19,300
Did you eat something?

126
00:12:20,130 --> 00:12:21,490
No, not yet.

127
00:12:22,250 --> 00:12:23,250
Are you hungry?

128
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:26,080
- Yeah, I'm starving.
- Really?

129
00:12:26,410 --> 00:12:27,510
- Yeah.
- You hungry?

130
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:29,080
Starving.

131
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:33,620
You're kind of incredible, Sara.

132
00:12:34,620 --> 00:12:35,620
Incredible?

133
00:12:36,390 --> 00:12:37,860
Top of the class,

134
00:12:38,160 --> 00:12:40,550
good-looking... you're
the star of the school.

135
00:12:42,640 --> 00:12:44,040
Are you fishing for a reward?

136
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:46,110
I'm not flattering you.

137
00:12:46,560 --> 00:12:48,319
Not just the Sara in this world,

138
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:50,270
but the one in the other world too.

139
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:53,940
If you'd met me in this world,

140
00:12:54,590 --> 00:12:55,990
would you still have fallen for me?

141
00:12:58,360 --> 00:12:59,360
Of course I would.

142
00:12:59,670 --> 00:13:01,510
Because you're so cute.

143
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,000
I am not cute.

144
00:13:03,980 --> 00:13:05,830
It's been a while, Master Sara.

145
00:13:09,750 --> 00:13:11,380
The Madam would like to see you.

146
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:13,280
She wants you to join her for dinner

147
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:14,750
and hear how you've been.

148
00:13:23,643 --> 00:13:25,253
Don't worry about me.

149
00:13:25,290 --> 00:13:26,490
I can get back on my own.

150
00:13:28,290 --> 00:13:29,650
Get home safe.

151
00:13:37,510 --> 00:13:38,510
This way, please.

152
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:25,399
(Sara: Let me know when you're home.)

153
00:14:25,400 --> 00:14:32,900
(Sara: Is something wrong?)

154
00:14:32,980 --> 00:14:34,790
The Chairwoman will be a little late.

155
00:14:35,640 --> 00:14:37,180
Would you like to rest in your room?

156
00:14:38,850 --> 00:14:39,850
I'll stay here.

157
00:14:40,760 --> 00:14:42,320
I'm leaving as soon as I'm done eating.

158
00:14:46,100 --> 00:14:53,600
(Fuu: I'm home! Have a
nice dinner with your mom.)

159
00:15:00,020 --> 00:15:01,300
That's so messy.

160
00:15:01,850 --> 00:15:02,850
Is that my fault?

161
00:15:03,140 --> 00:15:05,090
You okay? Did you catch a cold?

162
00:15:05,650 --> 00:15:06,800
Yeah, I'm fine.

163
00:15:07,290 --> 00:15:08,780
Do you want to go home and rest?

164
00:15:09,110 --> 00:15:11,080
But we have that group
project this afternoon.

165
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:13,840
Don't worry, we'll tell the professor.

166
00:15:14,730 --> 00:15:15,930
Does Sara know?

167
00:15:16,163 --> 00:15:17,373
Did you tell him you're sick?

168
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:20,750
No, he went back to his
family home yesterday.

169
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:22,000
Oh, but...

170
00:15:22,070 --> 00:15:23,190
Yeah, I know.

171
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:24,480
I won't say anything.

172
00:15:25,410 --> 00:15:27,240
Alright, hurry up and
eat so you can go home.

173
00:15:33,270 --> 00:15:34,289
That's gross.

174
00:15:34,290 --> 00:15:35,980
It wasn't me.

175
00:15:45,400 --> 00:15:46,600
Where are you going?

176
00:15:48,710 --> 00:15:49,710
I'm leaving.

177
00:15:50,630 --> 00:15:51,630
Please, wait.

178
00:15:52,220 --> 00:15:53,940
The Chairwoman has something to say to you.

179
00:15:58,270 --> 00:15:59,790
How much longer am I supposed to wait?

180
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:02,440
I'm going back.

181
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:04,020
The Chairwoman says

182
00:16:04,550 --> 00:16:06,220
you've breached the contract.

183
00:16:08,790 --> 00:16:10,290
This is a test

184
00:16:12,230 --> 00:16:14,680
to see if you'll follow orders.

185
00:16:16,703 --> 00:16:18,343
I think it's best if you just wait.

186
00:16:38,380 --> 00:16:40,080
How did you catch a cold?

187
00:16:40,210 --> 00:16:41,600
Were you staying up late again?

188
00:16:43,050 --> 00:16:44,050
Mom,

189
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:46,150
I've been sleeping better lately.

190
00:16:46,890 --> 00:16:48,990
Because I have someone to say goodnight to.

191
00:16:49,280 --> 00:16:50,280
Oh?

192
00:16:50,680 --> 00:16:52,690
Since when did you have someone like that?

193
00:16:54,800 --> 00:16:57,230
I'll tell you all about it
next time you're home.

194
00:17:04,560 --> 00:17:07,550
I really miss your tamagoyaki.

195
00:17:13,540 --> 00:17:14,540
Just kidding.

196
00:17:15,390 --> 00:17:16,609
I can make it myself now.

197
00:17:16,610 --> 00:17:19,260
Once I'm better, I'll
make a ton and eat my fill.

198
00:17:23,890 --> 00:17:24,890
Fuu...

199
00:17:28,100 --> 00:17:29,420
I should probably get some sleep.

200
00:17:29,850 --> 00:17:31,300
You should get some rest too, Mom.

201
00:17:32,040 --> 00:17:33,040
Goodnight.

202
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:02,420
My university grades are fine.

203
00:18:04,020 --> 00:18:06,680
I haven't done anything
to tarnish your reputation.

204
00:18:08,380 --> 00:18:08,840
And...

205
00:18:08,850 --> 00:18:11,800
I'm talking about the agreement
to stay away from your father.

206
00:18:13,090 --> 00:18:15,770
- I never signed any such agreement.
- But you broke it, didn't you?

207
00:18:19,440 --> 00:18:21,530
It's that man's influence, isn't it?

208
00:18:22,030 --> 00:18:24,690
Keeping someone so beneath you around.

209
00:18:26,080 --> 00:18:27,080
What?

210
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:29,020
Fuu Yotsuba.

211
00:18:32,010 --> 00:18:33,219
That's none of your business.

212
00:18:33,220 --> 00:18:35,810
I'm the one who decides what's my business.

213
00:18:36,010 --> 00:18:37,510
Not you.

214
00:18:39,830 --> 00:18:41,680
Is that what he told you?

215
00:18:42,556 --> 00:18:44,076
Is that why you're talking back to me?

216
00:18:46,523 --> 00:18:48,093
I won't see my father again.

217
00:19:04,050 --> 00:19:05,540
I'm very sorry.

218
00:19:11,530 --> 00:19:15,950
Just do as I say.

219
00:19:18,010 --> 00:19:19,840
Because your life

220
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:22,760
belongs to me.

221
00:19:50,580 --> 00:19:51,580
Hello?

222
00:19:52,660 --> 00:19:53,940
How was dinner?

223
00:19:55,270 --> 00:19:56,270
What's wrong?

224
00:19:57,300 --> 00:19:59,430
Your voice sounds a little off.

225
00:20:05,650 --> 00:20:06,930
When are you coming back?

226
00:20:10,690 --> 00:20:11,690
Are you feeling sick?

227
00:20:13,520 --> 00:20:16,690
Oh, I'm fine. I'm great, really.

228
00:20:18,080 --> 00:20:19,080
Alright.

229
00:20:19,530 --> 00:20:20,530
I believe you.

230
00:20:22,770 --> 00:20:24,100
Is there anything you want?

231
00:20:28,070 --> 00:20:29,170
Tamagoyaki.

232
00:20:32,470 --> 00:20:33,470
I'll bring some back.

233
00:20:34,990 --> 00:20:36,790
I'll call you later.

234
00:20:37,490 --> 00:20:38,590
Get some sleep.

235
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:40,410
It's really not like that.

236
00:20:41,120 --> 00:20:42,120
I know.

237
00:20:46,070 --> 00:20:47,070
Sara.

238
00:20:50,530 --> 00:20:51,530
Yeah?

239
00:20:55,560 --> 00:20:56,760
Hurry back.

240
00:20:57,670 --> 00:20:58,720
I'm lonely.

241
00:21:16,710 --> 00:21:17,710
Excuse me.

242
00:21:20,340 --> 00:21:22,060
Master Sara has already left.

243
00:21:22,790 --> 00:21:23,790
I see.

244
00:21:24,169 --> 00:21:25,169
Is that alright?

245
00:21:26,840 --> 00:21:29,620
Let him enjoy his little taste of freedom.

246
00:21:31,980 --> 00:21:35,360
He'll be paying for it
for the rest of his life.

247
00:21:39,470 --> 00:21:40,510
Fuu.

248
00:22:08,270 --> 00:22:09,890
Fuu, I'm here.

249
00:22:26,860 --> 00:22:27,860
Sara.

250
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:29,680
Thank goodness.

251
00:22:41,663 --> 00:22:42,863
I have a cold.

252
00:22:47,310 --> 00:22:48,800
Sorry I'm late.

253
00:22:52,730 --> 00:22:53,930
It's okay now.

254
00:22:56,140 --> 00:22:57,340
You've had a long day.

255
00:23:00,010 --> 00:23:01,460
Everything's going to be okay.

256
00:24:54,000 --> 00:24:55,730
That's a cheetah.

257
00:24:56,310 --> 00:24:57,820
Taiga senpai.

258
00:24:58,480 --> 00:25:00,640
Whoa! You scared the life out of me.

259
00:25:01,340 --> 00:25:03,070
Is this guy a ghost?

260
00:25:03,500 --> 00:25:04,730
I thought I saw a ghost.

261
00:25:07,390 --> 00:25:08,490
I'm very much real.

262
00:25:08,930 --> 00:25:09,930
Want to touch and see?

263
00:25:11,130 --> 00:25:12,130
Are you mocking me?

264
00:25:12,640 --> 00:25:13,640
Stop messing with me.
